tldr: The user requested a comprehensive aesthetic review and improvement for
  their sleep questionnaire app. The agent implemented a new sleep-themed color
  palette, redesigned the main form layout, polished UI components, and ensured
  consistent styling across all sections, including fixing a console error
  related to null input values and addressing user feedback on inconsistent
  report section colors.
overview: The user initiated a request to significantly enhance the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too
  generic. The agent began by conducting a thorough code review of existing
  styling, identifying areas such as the color palette, layout, and form
  elements as needing improvement. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced using OKLCH values, along with custom CSS utility classes for
  gradients and shadows. The main questionnaire form layout was redesigned with
  decorative background elements and a more engaging progress indicator. Key UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received a
  visual refresh with improved hover and selected states. All questionnaire
  sections were updated to reflect the new theme, replacing plain gray boxes
  with more refined card-style groupings. During the process, a console error
  related to  values being passed to input fields was identified and fixed
  by modifying the  component to safely handle such values. Following an
  initial round of changes, the user provided feedback on inconsistent card
  header colors in the report section, leading to further refinements to ensure
  all report cards used a unified sleep-themed gradient and all text colors were
  consistent with the new palette. The agent also standardized alert styling
  across the app with new utility classes and adjusted section border opacity
  for better visual definition. The overall outcome is a visually cohesive,
  professional, and calming application experience.
